			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Mezzing, Lulling, Looting - Questions From A Curious Bard<a name="13646"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 23 03 9:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mezzing:
<br />
I'd be curious to hear how various people approach this.  I have always felt awkward doing this properly.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" />
<br />
Here's my questions:
<br />
How many adds can we be expected to mezz?
<br />
What is the best way to target the adds?
<br />
(My biggest problem - I assist the main tank, see who he/she is attacking, then turn off auto attack, and either try to click the adds, or run close to them and F8... both are problematic when there is a lot of traffic)
<br />
Do you announce the mezz AS you are casting, or not until you see if it gets resisted or not?
<br />
Do you even attempt to swap from weapons to flute?
<br />

<br />
Lulling:
<br />
I'd also be curious to hear people's lull strategies too.
<br />
When I get called upon for crowd control, I feel like I'm making it up as I go along, and that's not a good thing.
<br />
Can you realistically lull more than 3 mobs?
<br />
In a room with more than 3, which mobs to you pick to lull?
<br />
Do you try to tell the puller which ones you are lulling, or do you announce which one they should pull?
<br />

<br />
Looting:
<br />
Oh, and one final question:
<br />
Do you think, given all the twisting a bard has to do, it is a little unreasonable to ask the bard to be a Main Looter as well during an LDoN?
<br />
With all the twisting going on, I find it hard enough to try to keep a basic level of communication going on with my group without having to worry about the looting.  But this has come up several times now - where melee classes, who have nothing better to do between battles then sit &amp; heal, have declined to do the looting duties.
<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-12.gif" border="0" alt="Mad" hspace="2" /> Grrrrr.
<br />
Maybe it's just me.
<br />

<br />
Curious to hear your input!
<br />

<br />
Cyanu
<br />
44th Song,
<br />
Kane Bayle Server.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
