		</table></td><td class="PanelBodyAlternate" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mezzing, Lulling, Looting - Questions From A Curious Bard<a name="13650"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 23 03 10:27 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Your questions seem to be in the context of playing a 40s bard in LDoN or an experience group, so I'll answer them based on my experience and opinion.  Answers for raids with a 60s bard might be different.  As always, your mileage may vary.
<br />

<br />
&gt; How many adds can we be expected to mezz? 
<br />

<br />
Three.  This gives you the opportunity to miss a note or two and still keep three mobs mesmerized.  I find that if I try to mez more, I start to miss song cycles, and the mobs start to wake up, and I get stunned, missing more song cycles, and then we usually die in a spectacular multi-mob wipeout.
<br />

<br />
&gt; What is the best way to target the adds? 
<br />

<br />
I use my mouse pointer and click on the mobs' feet.  Don't worry about the melee; they'll hit whatever they feel like hitting.  Just keep mezzing until the main assist makes up their mind, and the rest of the melee decide to assist the main tank.  Eventually.
<br />

<br />
&gt; Do you announce the mezz AS you are casting, or not until you see if it gets resisted or not? 
<br />

<br />
I annouce as soon as I am attempting to mez.  This allows careful players the opportunity to stop attacking the creature that I am trying to mez.  
<br />

<br />
I also use pronouns in my messages (%s, %o, etc) to clarify:
<br />

<br />
&quot;MEZ:  I am mesmerizing A Truculent Hoyden; stop hitting her already!&quot;
<br />

<br />
which are quite useful when you are swarmed in Mistmoore Catacombs and some people are hitting the boy vampire, and other people are hitting the girl vampire.  This technique is less useful in other dungeons with neuter mobs.
<br />

<br />
&gt; Do you even attempt to swap from weapons to flute? 
<br />

<br />
I strongly, strongly recommend purchasing or looting a primary-handed flute for LDoN.  That way you can have a weapon in your off-hand when you need to fight, but you'll always have the wind instrument bonus when you need it without having to juggle instruments and weapons in a pressure situation.  For the offhand I suggest a weapon with a CHR bonus or a harmony proc (Sainy's Dagger, Symphonic Saber) to enhance mez and mitigate mez aggro.
<br />

<br />
&gt; Can you realistically lull more than 3 mobs? 
<br />

<br />
Maybe a few more; probably not more than six.  Now that lull has been nerfed to last only a few song cycles, I re-apply lull before every pull.  Lull early and lull often.
<br />

<br />
&gt; In a room with more than 3, which mobs to you pick to lull? 
<br />

<br />
The nearest ones.  Aggro is distance based.  Always lull the closest mob first, that way if it resists and attacks, it will not run through other mobs on its way to you, aggroing them and adding them to the inevitable train.  &quot;Bard pull!&quot;
<br />

<br />
&gt; Do you try to tell the puller which ones you are lulling, or do you announce which one they should pull? 
<br />

<br />
Yes, I announce each as I lull so the people sitting on their butts have an idea about what kind of numbers we are facing in the next room.  The casters tend to act a bit more alert once they've seen the sixth lull message from a single room.  
<br />

<br />
I usually pull with snare/slow after I've lulled, but if someone else must be the puller (Shadowknights, Paladins), then I let them pick whichever one they want after I've announced lulls.
<br />

<br />
&gt; Do you think, given all the twisting a bard has to do, it is a little unreasonable to ask the bard to be a Main Looter as well during an LDoN? 
<br />

<br />
Absolutely unreasonable.  But if it's asked of you, just tell them you can master loot as long as you don't have to pull, crowd control, or twist.  That usually gets one of the healers to do the work.  </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
