			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mezzing, Lulling, Looting - Questions From A Curious Bard<a name="13651"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 23 03 10:31 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mezzing:
<br />
A bard can realistically twist 3 songs, maybe 4, so that's the number most bards can handle mezing, baring resists.  I find if I have one to mez, I try to keep up two of my regular battle twists.  If I have 2 to mez, one of my battle twists or manasong because it's going to be a long battle with limited mana breaks.
<br />

<br />
To target, I normally do it in first person because I'm lazy, but it's best to use an overhead view to be able to tartet mobs easier.  You could try F8 as a default, and if it's damaged that's the one the group is killing and choose another. I do it, though awkwardly.  
<br />

<br />
One note on targeting, get used to using the &quot;toggle last two targets&quot; command (I remapped mine to the ~ key for easy twisting), and position myself BETWEEN the two (example) mobs. That say I can melee, twist 2 songs and keep the mob behind me mezed using the ~ key to change targets right before I click mez, then change right back to the melee action.  Takes a bit of practice but not bad once you get the hang of it.
<br />

<br />
I normally tell the group I'll be mezing adds so be patient, then expect them to remember for the duration. Normally works. The message gets annoying, to me at least, when you remez something 2 or 3 times a battle.  As for tell the puller? I AM the puller, always nowadays.  It is a problem sometimes to tell your group if your MA doesn't assist before you start mezing.  /shrug
<br />

<br />
Lulling:
<br />
As the puller, I lull the closest first, then move back, I'm afraid for resists and hope they don't run over my lulled mob so I can avoid wipes.  At least lull the one closest to the one you will be pulling and pull the closest mob to you. I normally lull a room, pull one back to my group, go back rinse repeat til there's one left in the room the call the group up to fight it there.  Even with the 5 tick lull, I can lull 5 or so, but make sure the lull on the next closest is fresh.  I get an add or two on occasion now where I didn't before, but it's all good.
<br />

<br />
Looting:
<br />
Despite my innate high charisma for selling, the chanter or cleric is always the ML in my groups. When your're pulling, hasting, slowing, DSing, snaring, buffing and CCing, there is NO time to loot for the group.  It would slow you down considerably. If you must loot, click manasong before you loot as you cant twist and activily loot a corpse at the same time.
<br />

<br />
Sorry for the long post, think I hit the high points.  Hope it helps,
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547835">Maestro Sinfonian's gear... (inspect me)</a> </span></td>
