		</table></td><td class="PanelBodyAlternate" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mezzing, Lulling, Looting - Questions From A Curious Bard<a name="13652"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 23 03 10:33 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mezzing - 3 is all I can handle.  2 is easy because of tab targeting but then I am not adding any damage and I can only buff with one song - all in all I prefer not to be the main crowd control guy.  It has been suggested that you switch to 3rd person view to make targeting easier.  I find 3rd person view very awkward - however I can work the top view very well - just lean it forward until you are at the bottom of the screen and you get a pretty good field of view.
<br />

<br />
Lulling - I never lulled everything in the room before the nerf err patch so not much changed for me.  A lot depends upon the situation but lull the guys next to the guys you want to pull and dont pull through other mobs.  This strategy means you cant pull boss mobs from the middle of the room but it does let you pull safely.  Note that in may situations you cannot avoid pulling 2 - so pull the 2 and mez one.
<br />

<br />
Looting - I never loot as you cant pull and loot.  I always want the rogue to loot - they are pickpocketing anyway so at least make them split it.  BTW I dont really like the idea of a ML on casual LDoN adventures - it is too tempting for loot whores and they are more common than you think.
<br />

<br />
Tin.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
