			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mezzing, Lulling, Looting - Questions From A Curious Bard<a name="13776"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 24 03 10:46 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>  &gt;Mezzing: 
<br />
  &gt;How many adds can we be expected to mezz?
<br />
3, can do more, but one will always be breaking.  Keep in mind, every mob you have to mezz drops one or two songs out of a twist.
<br />

<br />
 &gt;What is the best way to target the adds? 
<br />
Whenever possible I use third person view, think it's F9 three times and set it way high and back so I can see the camp and all the adds.  This allows me to target the adds without stopping melee.  Remember, you dont have to have the add targeted for the entire song duration to mezz it.  simply target the mob near the end of a song in your normal twist, then start singing mez on it. Once you have the mezz song going, you can target the MT's mob to melee again, or target another add to mezz.  What the group sees is you nearly non stop meleeing while keeping 2-3 songs going, and mezzing adds at the same time.  If they dont say WTF, how do you do that, then they either arent paying attention, or they have grouped with you before!
<br />
 
<br />
 &gt;Do you announce the mezz AS you are casting, or not until you see if it gets resisted or not?
<br />
I announce as I am casting:  &quot;Attempting to mezz %t&quot;  
<br />

<br />
 &gt;Do you even attempt to swap from weapons to flute? 
<br />
I have epic, so no.  But when I DIDNT have epic, I still didnt bother.  In my experience, it wasnt worth the time, unless I KNEW the mobs were very MR, or found out thru experience that I would get a lot of resists.  In that case, I just whipped out the flute whenever I saw an add, and never swapped weapon back in during fight.  Lazy?  Yeah, but instrument swapping sucks!
<br />

<br />
 &gt;When I get called upon for crowd control, I feel like I'm making it up as I go along, and that's not a good thing. 
<br />
WOOT!!  If you are making it up as you go along, then you are kicking serious a$!  No other class &quot;makes it up as we go along&quot; like Bards.  Welcome to being the Jack of all trades class, revel in your ability to improvise and keep your groups alive!
<br />
 &gt;Can you realistically lull more than 3 mobs? 
<br />
Havent had a serious lull session since the patch, but I would imagine 2 is the most with the new lull duration.  5 ticks isnt much.
<br />

<br />
 &gt;In a room with more than 3, which mobs to you pick to lull?
<br />
The caster if possible.  Pull them last.  And if it is a healing caster, then you need to pull the mob out of range of it, or else you get the mob CHd while you are fighting it.  That sucks.  But pull casters last.  Melee mobs wont stand there for 15 ticks casting on you after you aggro it, while lull breaks off all the other mobs and they rush you.  Lull the caster, pull the melee mobs.  Then you can rush the caster.  Or stand there, sing resists, and laugh as he wastes his mana on you
<br />
 
<br />
 &gt;Do you try to tell the puller which ones you are lulling, or do you announce which one they should pull? 
<br />
I have never been in a situation where I was lulling and someone else was pulling.  Just do it yourself, none of our songs get us so much aggro that the MT cant yank it off us as it is inc.  If we do take a few shots till the MT wakes up, hey, that is why we are a plate class!
<br />

<br />
As for your last question, no way in h*ll would I ever ML. 
<br />
I am waaay to busy.
<br />
And I dont think any other class normally carries as much crap around as a bard.
<br />
h*ll, look at my magelo, with Lockpicks, SS Helm, SS Gaunts, 4 instruments, a few specialty weapons, and other situational gear or items, I have like 1 1/2 bags that I can put loot in.  everything else is taken.
<br />
If course, some of that stuff is just for play.  Like the mammoth meat, I carry that around just to link.
<br />
&quot;Hey, would anyone want some of my Mammoth meat&quot;?
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
