				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Mezzing, Lulling, Looting - Questions From A Curious Bard<a name="15580"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 14 04 11:00 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm just starting out in my barddom, and I did my first LDoN last Sunday at level 17. (I was PLed up to 20 to catch up with my regular Sunday play group of RL friends.) Our group consists of an SK, enchanter, cleric, shaman, wizard and my bard. All of us are playing different characters to our mians, and our cleric and shaman are husband and wife and generally just grouped duo with their mains. Therefore, we're spending half our time teaching them their roles in a group. (Not that this is a problem, because we're all friends and they want to learn how to play correctly.)
<br />

<br />
Because I only have the single lull, and we have an SK, and we have an enchanter, I haven't been asked to be the puller or the main CC. But I can answer your LDoN looting question, at least at the newbie level.
<br />

<br />
Right now, I'm bogging myself down with backpacks to collect all the newbie loot we're getting because my main is recovering from buying BSS and I can't spend money to twink out an alt. So I was the only one who was able to loot the adventure. To tell you the truth, it wasn't that bad. But then again, as I said before, I'm not asked to be one of the starring roles right now. (That'll probably change when I get my AoE lull.)
<br />

<br />
What I was doing was keeping one spell going after a creature went down. It was generally the health regen spell. I figured as soon as I was done looting, I could just begin on my second twist -- haste. I usually had looting done before we started on the next mob, so the seconds we missed by not having haste going straight away was negligable. Now that I've hit 20, it'll probably be my mana regen that keeps going.
<br />

<br />
But I agree with everyone above. I think one I get some better spells to pull with, I would not be able to loot because of having to focus on twisting spells while pulling.</span></td>
